                <img src="/images/ENLOGO.png" alt="College of Engineering Logo" class="logo-image" />
            </div>

            <!-- Main Title -->
            <h1 class="main-title">HELP CENTER</h1>

            <!-- Intro -->
            <div class="content-area">
                <p>
                    Welcome to the Help Center for the <strong>Digital Borrowing System</strong>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This page will guide you through the system's features, procedures, and frequently asked questions.
                    It is designed to help students, professors, and administrators understand how to use the platform efficiently.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Procedures Section -->
            <h2 class="section-title">Procedures</h2>
            <div class="procedure-section">
                <h3>For Students</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Login using your student account credentials.</li>
                    <li>Select a department you want to borrow materials from.</li>
                    <li>Choose the items you want to borrow and set their quantities.</li>
                    <li>Add them to your borrowing form.</li>
                    <li>Submit the form to the professor handling your subject code.</li>
                    <li>Wait for approval. Once approved, you can proceed to claim your borrowed items.</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>For Professors</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Login using your professor account credentials.</li>
                    <li>Review pending borrowing forms submitted by students.</li>
                    <li>Approve or disapprove the requests based on validity and item availability.</li>
                    <li>Approved forms are then sent to the administrator for final verification.</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>For Administrators</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Login using your admin account credentials.</li>
                    <li>View approved forms from professors.</li>
                    <li>Accept or deny requests depending on stock and policy.</li>
                    <li>Update the database with borrowing records for tracking and history purposes.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Section -->
            <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>
            <div class="faq-section">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>1. What is the Digital Borrowing System?</h3>
                    <p>The Digital Borrowing System is an online platform that allows students to request, borrow, and track materials from different departments efficiently.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>2. Who can use the system?</h3>
                    <p>The system can be accessed by three main users: students, professors, and administrators â€” each having specific roles and permissions.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>3. How do I know if my borrowing request is approved?</h3>
                    <p>You will receive a status update in your account once your professor and the administrator approve your borrowing form.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>4. Can I cancel my borrowing request after submitting?</h3>
                    <p>Yes. As long as your request is still pending and not yet approved by your professor, you can cancel it from your account dashboard.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>5. What happens if an item I need is unavailable?</h3>
                    <p>The system will notify you of item unavailability. You can either wait until it's restocked or choose another available item.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>6. Is my personal data secure?</h3>
                    <p>Yes. All user information and borrowing records are protected through secure database management and authentication features.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>7. What should I do if I forget my password?</h3>
                    <p>Click on the "Forgot Password" option on the login page. Follow the verification process to reset your password safely.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>8. Who should I contact for technical issues?</h3>
                    <p>If you encounter bugs or errors, contact the system administrator or your department's IT support team for assistance.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

